parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the hybrid brake system can cause the brakes to fail, leading to accidents or near-accidents, and potentially resulting in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The ABS and brake warning lights illuminate
the brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brakes take longer to stop the vehicle
the vehicle vibrates or pulsates when braking
the brakes grab or release suddenly
and the vehicle may coast or not stop at all.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause the steering wheel to become difficult to turn, leading to loss of control and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The power steering assist fault message is displayed
the steering wheel becomes difficult to turn
the steering wheel vibrates or shakes
the vehicle is hard to steer
and the power steering warning light illuminates.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the hybrid system can cause the vehicle to suddenly lose power, leading to a loss of control and increased risk of accidents, especially on high-speed roads.
symptoms: The "Stop Safely Now" warning message appears on the dashboard
the vehicle suddenly loses power
the engine stalls
the vehicle jerks or hesitates
the power steering and engine shut down
and the vehicle may not restart.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the throttle body assembly can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to a loss of control and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The "Stop Safely Now" warning message appears on the dashboard
the vehicle suddenly loses power
the engine stalls
and the vehicle may not restart.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the hybrid cooling system can cause the vehicle to suddenly lose power, leading to a loss of control and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The "Stop Safely Now" warning message appears on the dashboard
the vehicle suddenly loses power
the engine stalls
and the vehicle may not restart.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the cooling system can cause the engine to overheat, leading to a sudden loss of power, stalling, and potentially causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The "Stop Safely Now" warning light illuminates on the instrument panel
the vehicle stalls or loses power while driving
the temperature light illuminates
the vehicle is unable to accelerate or maintain speed
and the engine shuts off without warning.
